---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Multi-tool Orchestration | Enhanced Task Completion">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--primary">MCP Tool Chaining</span>
        <h1>Multi-tool Orchestration</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The agent dynamically chains 5 tools across the Order Management MCP server,
          parallelizing independent calls and keeping the user informed at every step.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Follow along</h2>
        <p>Open the chat UI in another tab, then follow each step below.</p>

        <div class="turn">
          <div class="turn__label">Step 1</div>
          <div class="turn__you">
            <span class="turn__who">You say:</span>
            <div class="try-prompt">
              <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Hi, I'm Sarah Mitchell. I ordered some Sony headphones recently but they arrived with a crackling sound in the left ear. I'd like to return them. Also, can you check where my other order is, the Kindle I ordered last week?</blockquote>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="turn__expect">
            <span class="turn__who">The agent:</span>
            <ul>
              <li>Identifies two tasks: process a return and check an order status</li>
              <li>Calls <code>search_orders</code> to find all orders for Sarah Mitchell</li>
              <li>Calls <code>get_order</code> &times;3 in parallel to fetch details</li>
              <li>Identifies the headphones (ORD-10421) and Kindle (ORD-10422)</li>
              <li>Calls <code>request_return</code> + <code>get_shipment</code> in parallel</li>
              <li>Returns the return ID, refund details, label link, and Kindle status</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Screenshot -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What it looks like</h2>
        <div class="scenario__screenshot">
          <img src={`${base}images/scenario-tools.png`} alt="Multi-tool orchestration in the chat UI" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Why it matters -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Dependency awareness</h3>
            <p>The agent knows it needs order IDs from <code>search_orders</code> before calling <code>get_order</code>. It sequences dependent calls automatically.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Parallel execution</h3>
            <p>Independent calls (fetching multiple orders, return + shipment) run simultaneously, reducing total response time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Intermediate narration</h3>
            <p>The user sees progress messages between tool call batches, "Found 3 orders, pulling details...", so they know the agent is working.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .scenario { padding: var(--space-3xl) 0; }
  .back { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--c-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
  .back:hover { color: var(--c-primary); }
  .scenario__header { max-width: 680px; }
  .scenario__header h1 { margin-top: var(--space-md); }
  .scenario__lead { margin-top: var(--space-lg); font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; }
  .scenario__section { margin-top: var(--space-3xl); }
  .scenario__section h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); }
  .scenario__section > p { color: var(--c-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); }
  .scenario__screenshot { border: 1px solid var(--c-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
  .scenario__screenshot img { width: 100%; }
  .turn { margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); padding: var(--space-lg); background: var(--c-surface); border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); }
  .turn__label { font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--c-purple); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .turn__who { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--c-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; display: block; margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
  .turn__you { margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .turn__you .try-prompt { background: var(--c-surface-raised); border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-md); }
  .turn__you .try-prompt__text { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--c-text); line-height: 1.6; border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary); padding-left: var(--space-md); margin: 0; }
  .turn__expect ul { padding-left: 20px; margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; }
  .turn__expect li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .turn__expect code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85em; background: var(--c-surface-raised); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle); }
  .value-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-lg); }
  .value-card { padding: var(--space-lg); background: var(--c-surface-raised); border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .value-card h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
  .value-card p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
</style>
